Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.33,0:00:04.07,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A racing second hand, a shining comet!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.07,0:00:07.54,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Conan's logic is good medicine\Nfor hearts tired by modern society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.54,0:00:11.07,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today is the first two-hour special!\NTry your hand at the two cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.07,0:00:12.61,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.61,0:00:14.44,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.44,0:00:16.89,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.98,0:01:46.52,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Agasa Residence
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.65,0:01:46.52,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}C'mon! Hear me out, Shin{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-chan{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.52,0:01:49.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah. I'm listening, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.60,0:01:56.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yusaku left early this morning and came home totally drunk again!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.86,0:01:57.61,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yukiko Kudo\NShin'ichi's mother (Actress)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.06,0:01:57.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, he makes me so mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.61,0:02:01.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't help it. Dad's a popular novelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.87,0:02:04.47,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He has to socialize with all kinds of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.47,0:02:08.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose lipstick is on his shirt, then?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.12,0:02:11.33,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yusaku Kudo\NWorld-renowned mystery writer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.31,0:02:11.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm so mad! I'm gonna cheat on him, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.33,0:02:14.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:16.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm busy right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.02,0:02:17.27,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait! Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.19,0:02:22.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? I assume that was Yukiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.76,0:02:25.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was complaining about her marital strife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.76,0:02:29.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad coming home drunk, dad cheating on her...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.10,0:02:30.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Cheating?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.90,0:02:33.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.07,0:02:38.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All he thinks about is mysteries.\NHe'd never be that good-for-nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:42.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, their fights are almost annual events. No point in worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.81,0:02:47.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They're so close they argue a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.15,0:02:50.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, how are things with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.08,0:02:51.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.62,0:02:55.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.\NAre you getting along well?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.56,0:03:00.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She gets mad every time I call her.\N"When will you finally be back?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.33,0:03:05.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we almost see too much\Nof each other every single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.37,0:03:09.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, don't be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.67,0:03:14.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not take a break from your cases\Nand go somewhere with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.84,0:03:17.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Autumn {\i1}is{\i0} the season for love!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.98,0:03:21.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The season for love indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.78,0:03:24.78,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mouri Detective Agency"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.45,0:03:28.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'm back!\N- You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.46,0:03:30.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mind your own business!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.32,0:03:36.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that tone? Here I am, trying to give you another client.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.33,0:03:35.21,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Eri Kisaki\NRan's mother (Attorney)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.40,0:03:39.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As if I need your help!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.13,0:03:41.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.23,0:03:46.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't blame me when business isn't going well, Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.84,0:03:52.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, thank you for worrying about me, Great Attorney!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.95,0:03:56.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}These two are having their own marital spat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.52,0:03:59.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Autumn's the season of love? Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.76,0:04:04.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Autumn's the season of hunger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.96,0:04:08.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hurry home, Ran. I'm starving...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.73,0:04:12.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.40,0:04:13.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.18,0:04:14.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.97,0:04:18.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for Conan? He's asleep on the sofa.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:19.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.31,0:04:23.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! Dozing off in a place like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:26.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.51,0:04:29.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes! I'll make something right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.05,0:04:32.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! At least take your glasses off when you sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.79,0:04:39.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This face... I've seen it somewhere, long ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:49.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.27,0:04:53.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? G-Give back my glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.64,0:04:57.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, you're always wearing glasses, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.48,0:05:00.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when sleeping or taking a bath. Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.81,0:05:05.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Isn't that obvious? I have bad eyesight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.22,0:05:09.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-And I can't relax without them always on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.16,0:05:14.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.73,0:05:18.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Might this be the Mouri Detective Agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.30,0:05:20.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.10,0:05:26.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So you're the one she shamelessly sent to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.17,0:05:26.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.97,0:05:27.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's "she"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.94,0:05:32.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom, Eri Kisaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Right, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.75,0:05:36.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? No way! Mom asked for your help?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.68,0:05:39.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You're both getting along!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.85,0:05:43.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This means you're pretty much back together, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.59,0:05:46.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You set this up, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.46,0:05:50.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it seemed strange that she'd call me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.83,0:05:55.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kids shouldn't be meddling with adults' affairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.20,0:06:01.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so wrong with doing this?! I want Mom to come back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.24,0:06:03.44,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You've made things even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.44,0:06:06.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what brings you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.74,0:06:12.41,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Nanae Tsukumo (42)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.91,0:06:12.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's actually about my husband, who died one week ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.41,0:06:16.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Died? You don't think he was killed, do you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:19.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I think it was suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.76,0:06:21.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.13,0:06:22.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.80,0:06:28.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On that day, one week ago, I left him alone at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.87,0:06:33.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't find him when I returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.07,0:06:37.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I worriedly checked his special room in the basement...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.38,0:06:44.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where I found his cold body lying on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:46.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had swallowed poison...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.12,0:06:48.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What sort of poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.05,0:06:51.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A policeman called it "aconitine", or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.73,0:06:53.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aconitine?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.73,0:06:56.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.46,0:07:00.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A type of poison that causes denervation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.03,0:07:03.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's found in the leaves and roots of wolfsbane.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.07,0:07:05.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just 2 milligrams is lethal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.17,0:07:09.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a powerful toxin that causes death minutes after ingestion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.94,0:07:12.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But where would you come across that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:14.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mountains are full of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.81,0:07:18.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wolfsbane is used in Chinese medicines,\Nminus the poison, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.85,0:07:20.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I mean you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.95,0:07:21.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.72,0:07:23.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.62,0:07:29.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Television! A monster in Kamen Yaiba\Nmentioned it the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.36,0:07:34.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "I'll kill you with this aconitine,\Nextracted from wolfsbane!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.97,0:07:39.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've been a thoughtful monster to explain the poison like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.74,0:07:43.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's no such monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.18,0:07:47.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, were you the only one who found the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.55,0:07:50.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I was with my husband's three pupils.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.62,0:07:52.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pupils?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.45,0:07:56.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, my husband and I are both magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.86,0:08:01.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband, Motoyasu Tsukumo, was maybe even world-renowned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.56,0:08:01.52,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Motoyasu Tsukumo
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.83,0:08:03.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Motoyasu Tsukumo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.53,0:08:08.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know him! He was on the news! They said a great magician had died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.20,0:08:11.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All you ever watch is horseracing, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.47,0:08:16.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember? We all went to his magic show a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:20.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, I think there's a photo of us with Tsukumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.05,0:08:24.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was at that show that I met your wife, Kisaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.45,0:08:26.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. So that's why you're here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.79,0:08:33.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Kisaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has been our attorney ever since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.86,0:08:36.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Here we are! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.53,0:08:39.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait, could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.44,0:08:51.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find the photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.38,0:08:54.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I guess I was mistaken!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.52,0:08:59.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say! You should ask about those three pupils!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.75,0:09:01.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Would that be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.38,0:09:03.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.12,0:09:07.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,First, is Kazumi Sanada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, our magic troupe's ace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:11.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They say he's to take over for my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.20,0:09:15.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, is Mako Miyoshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. She's strong-minded, but greatly skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.64,0:09:19.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no better female magician in Japan than her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.37,0:09:21.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lastly, is Yuji Momochi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.64,0:09:25.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't been a pupil for very long and isn't as skilled as the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.28,0:09:28.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he shows great promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.21,0:09:32.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all wonderful youngsters, and all three live with us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.15,0:09:35.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and practice magic every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.26,0:09:38.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, where were they that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:41.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They were with me at a Beika Hotel dinner show,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.59,0:09:44.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,doing magic for the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.93,0:09:47.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband was supposed to come too,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.37,0:09:49.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he said he didn't do cheap work...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.84,0:09:53.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, those three were at home before leaving for the show, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:56.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't they have had the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ce to poison him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.84,0:09:58.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.44,0:10:02.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband died while the show was happening, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.18,0:10:06.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, couldn't they have secretly given him the poison in a capsule?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.15,0:10:10.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, my husband would've called for help after noticing the poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.99,0:10:12.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a phone in the basement,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.99,0:10:15.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the door unlocks easily from the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.83,0:10:17.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What about sleeping pills?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing like that was found in his autopsy, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:26.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There were no strangle marks, everything in the house was locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.81,0:10:30.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and there were absolutely no signs of entry or exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.01,0:10:32.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that means it could only be a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.95,0:10:35.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.72,0:10:39.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I just can't imagine my husband committing suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.79,0:10:42.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By which you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.16,0:10:47.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow is our daughter Ayano's birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.46,0:10:51.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He even got her present a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.30,0:10:56.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't wait to give it to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.04,0:10:58.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that sound suicidal to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.91,0:11:01.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the only unusual thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.27,0:11:06.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found this on his desk in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.11,0:11:09.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.25,0:11:13.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ace of Spades and a Jack are stuck together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:18.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The police pulled them apart, but there was nothing written inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.83,0:11:23.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I put them back together to show to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.13,0:11:26.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it isn't just a magic prop?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.13,0:11:29.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But my husband never really did card tricks,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.54,0:11:32.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I've never seen a prop like this before!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.34,0:11:35.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Let's just go to her house for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.48,0:11:38.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're always saying, "Let's go!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.75,0:11:41.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the only one going. You butt out, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.55,0:11:44.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on! Take Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.65,0:11:49.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He might be helpful! He knows all sorts of unusual things!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.96,0:11:51.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.96,0:11:54.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.43,0:11:56.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.03,0:11:58.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine! But you better behave yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.73,0:12:00.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We will!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.64,0:12:14.02,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,0)}"With Shin'ichi at a magic show..."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.80,0:12:19.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.97,0:12:22.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What an impressive mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.17,0:12:28.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! The late Motoyasu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was a world-renowned magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.55,0:12:30.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.25,0:12:31.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.55,0:12:34.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, where is the basement room\Nwhere your husband died?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.85,0:12:35.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.55,0:12:36.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.59,0:12:39.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Momochi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.26,0:12:41.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.73,0:12:45.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.06,0:12:48.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You appear to be greatly troubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.64,0:12:48.72,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuji Momochi (25)\NMagician
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.72,0:12:50.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.54,0:12:53.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no use hiding it. I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:56.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you have a pigeon in your hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.97,0:12:58.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.98,0:13:03.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it's your turn! Are you a new student?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.11,0:13:04.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.62,0:13:07.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, this is Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.79,0:13:10.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! The famous detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.19,0:13:12.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what is he doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.19,0:13:14.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You can't tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:19.53,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Mako Miyoshi (20)\NMagician
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.43,0:13:21.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's obviously here to investigate Motoyasu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.50,0:13:23.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Mr. Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.27,0:13:24.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.35,0:13:26.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Little boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.57,0:13:29.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and buxom girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.17,0:13:30.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Buxom?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.58,0:13:37.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}White...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.82,0:13:39.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.77,0:13:41.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.39,0:13:44.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You should at least use that many pigeons!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.06,0:13:45.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.39,0:13:49.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, what is a detective doing here? Wasn't his death a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.69,0:13:52.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because he wasn't the type to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.90,0:13:56.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, there are those strange cards. Or so I'd surmise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.73,0:13:57.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.67,0:13:59.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, these.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.30,0:14:05.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These strange cards were on the desk in the basement where he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.84,0:14:10.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the Ace of Spades and the Jack\Nthat were stuck together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.92,0:14:15.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, isn't this just a prop?\NPlus, the police said it was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.92,0:14:20.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes. There's nothing to find now,\Neven if you scoured the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:22.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.26,0:14:24.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.73,0:14:31.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is the fact there is now only one genius here instead of two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.49,0:14:31.67,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazumi Sanada (27)\NMagician
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.67,0:14:33.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you! You ripped up important evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.97,0:14:39.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. The real one is in your jacket pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.65,0:14:43.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute. Aren't you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.82,0:14:47.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's him! The genius magician who dressed up as the Kaito Kid
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.82,0:14:52.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,on that ship during the 60th anniversary party of the Suzuki {\i1}zaibatsu{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.62,0:14:54.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.26,0:14:56.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kazumi Sanada, at your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.33,0:15:04.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be wise to leave soon, unless you want to tarnish your reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.34,0:15:07.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems pretty indifferent to the fact\Nhis magic instructor just died...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.51,0:15:09.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.77,0:15:14.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? He used cards with different patterns just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.55,0:15:18.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He'd never normally do this. He's a perfectionist...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.42,0:15:23.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Sanada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s taken this pretty hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.55,0:15:27.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He looked up to my husband almost as a father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.23,0:15:29.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}These are the three pupils, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.23,0:15:30.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.76,0:15:34.30,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano Tsukumo (6)\NMotoyasu Tsukumo's daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.23,0:15:33.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you in Class A?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.10,0:15:35.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here? Are you here to visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.77,0:15:38.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we have some business here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.60,0:15:39.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of business?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.80,0:15:44.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh. So this is her house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.18,0:15:50.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one who has business here.\NHe just came along, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.52,0:15:53.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, in that case, want to go shopping with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.12,0:15:54.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.02,0:15:57.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mommy and I are just about to go buy an outfit
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.05,0:15:59.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,for my birthday party tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.26,0:16:02.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You got my invitation too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.33,0:16:04.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, so I did...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.20,0:16:06.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Let's go, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.14,0:16:07.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.04,0:16:09.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.00,0:16:13.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s busy right now!\NMaybe some other time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.77,0:16:17.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Kids should play with kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.41,0:16:23.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano. I'm sorry, but I can't go shopping today, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.95,0:16:26.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you promised, Mommy! You're a liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.68,0:16:32.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy is, too! My birthday is tomorrow, but he's still overseas!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.66,0:16:36.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're all a bunch of liars! I hate you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:45.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, will you go with me?\NI'll coordinate your outfit for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.40,0:16:46.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.74,0:16:48.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to bother you, Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.97,0:16:53.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, everyone! Back to your cage!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.84,0:16:55.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.75,0:16:59.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You still haven't told her her father is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.52,0:17:03.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I told her he's doing a show overseas...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.19,0:17:07.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? This isn't my pigeon. It's Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.12,0:17:10.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange for her to mistake her pigeons...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.93,0:17:13.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Her teacher's death must be hard on her, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.86,0:17:14.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.73,0:17:20.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And magicians are supposed to be good at concealing themselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.04,0:17:23.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only one who doesn't seem any different!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.47,0:17:26.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just recently became a pupil, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.64,0:17:28.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm going to get dinner ready now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.88,0:17:30.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.98,0:17:32.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does he always make the meals?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.88,0:17:36.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our custom is that the newest pupil always makes the meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.92,0:17:38.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.39,0:17:42.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, let us see the basement room where your husband died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.26,0:17:53.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what exactly is this basement room?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.03,0:17:55.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was my husband's special room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.37,0:17:59.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He would always hole up in here and research new magic tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.67,0:18:02.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His pupils seemed to use it lately, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.91,0:18:04.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those photographs?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.18,0:18:06.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My husband's students.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.04,0:18:10.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, even those who set out on their own or gave up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.65,0:18:14.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, miss. Who's that guy with the black hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.29,0:18:16.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's Kinoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.96,0:18:19.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a genius among geniuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.92,0:18:22.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, he died in his youth 14 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.86,0:18:25.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in a training accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:26.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.93,0:18:30.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's the only photo without dust on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.07,0:18:32.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wondered if someone had been taking care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.87,0:18:38.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're right. Was it my husband?\NHe was especially fond of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.71,0:18:43.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so this is where he swallowed the poison and collapsed?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.62,0:18:47.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The room is still exactly as it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.35,0:18:53.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those cards were in the pile of cards on this desk. As was the glue.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.10,0:19:02.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an unusually thick wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.50,0:19:07.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He enjoyed classical music, and always listened to it in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.91,0:19:11.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had the room soundproofed so he could play the music loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.58,0:19:16.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, nobody would be able to hear shouts coming from this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.85,0:19:18.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.68,0:19:21.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the door can be easily unlocked from the inside
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.69,0:19:25.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,even when locked from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.26,0:19:29.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He would've gone outside to get help\Nif he realized he was poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.79,0:19:33.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the fact that he stayed in the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.33,0:19:36.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam. Suicide is the only possibility I can think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.87,0:19:37.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.60,0:19:39.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.44,0:19:42.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See, look at the body mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.44,0:19:45.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His hands are by his side, in a well-mannered way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.74,0:19:48.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On TV and stuff, when someone is poisoned,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.35,0:19:51.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,don't they put their hands to their throat or chest like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.88,0:19:54.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, a policeman did say
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.69,0:19:57.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the body seemed a bit odd\Nfor someone who was poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.82,0:20:02.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When you found his body,\Nyou're sure he hadn't been strangled?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.59,0:20:03.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.63,0:20:07.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When all four of us found him,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.17,0:20:08.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we panicked and hurried to call an ambulance,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.97,0:20:12.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but they said no one had used rope on him at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.70,0:20:15.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, couldn't he have been strangled with a thin thread?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.87,0:20:18.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, like what they use in magic tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.54,0:20:22.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense. Even if you couldn't see it itself, it'd still leave a mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.18,0:20:26.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If there were such a mark,\Nthe cops would've found it long ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.29,0:20:30.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Rings?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.19,0:20:33.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. When he died, was he wearing these rings?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.96,0:20:38.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. His best trick involved using invisible strings on his rings
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.20,0:20:40.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to make things seem alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.93,0:20:45.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had probably been practicing it that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.20,0:20:48.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he only had the rings on.\NThere weren't any strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.41,0:20:50.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, then that's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.74,0:20:51.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Relief?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.71,0:20:55.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, if the strings got{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} tan{\r}gled up behind him,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.81,0:20:58.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he wouldn't be able to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.72,0:21:03.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? It's hard to get up if you can't use your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.66,0:21:06.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And using the doorknob would be hard, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.49,0:21:08.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.16,0:21:12.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband had rings on both hands tied with string or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.06,0:21:14.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His thumbs, most likely!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:17.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Evidence of this would remain on the body, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.47,0:21:19.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, by cutting that string before the police arrived,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.64,0:21:25.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would look like he had ordinary ring marks on his fingers!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.24,0:21:29.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband was poisoned before you and the pupils left!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.05,0:21:32.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The string was cut by someone when the body was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.38,0:21:33.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,probably during all the commotion!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.99,0:21:36.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you're saying my husband was—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.49,0:21:40.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Your husband was murdered!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.02,0:21:45.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,By one of the three who found his body with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.06,0:21:46.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.53,0:21:49.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do those cards mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.40,0:21:52.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the Ace and Jack that were lying over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.04,0:21:55.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet! I'm trying to figure that out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.64,0:21:58.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, there was a phone in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.41,0:22:02.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even without thumbs, it shouldn't be too hard to press the buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.61,0:22:04.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.72,0:22:07.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, speaking of the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.42,0:22:12.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when we found the body, I rushed upstairs to call an ambulance,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.52,0:22:18.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I didn't notice it right away,\Nbut this phone was buried in cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.10,0:22:19.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Buried?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.66,0:22:24.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! The killer hid the phone!\NTo keep the victim from using it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.90,0:22:29.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, wouldn't it still be easy to find\Nif you tried hard enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.44,0:22:32.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.04,0:22:36.18,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is the phone in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.18,0:22:40.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister. Let me see those cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.32,0:22:45.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See this symbol here? It's the same shape as the cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.42,0:22:46.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The redial button...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.99,0:22:51.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! These cards are a dying message from your husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.00,0:22:53.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,telling us to press the redial button!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.97,0:22:57.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If my guess is right, it should connect
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.34,0:23:00.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to someone your husband left a message with.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.41,0:23:06.54,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This number is not in use.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.54,0:23:07.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.31,0:23:12.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The police found that number too,\Nbut it was nonsense,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.05,0:23:15.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we assumed it was\Nmy daughter playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.02,0:23:16.49,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.49,0:23:18.89,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What are these numbers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.89,0:23:22.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, kid. What are you writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.03,0:23:25.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? A code?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.93,0:23:29.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"One two six eight seven one three two four eight nine..."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.67,0:23:32.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.00,0:23:34.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose way?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.94,0:23:43.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute! Could these numbers mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.81,0:23:52.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now I get it! That's how this code works!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.05,0:23:55.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In which case, this code means...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.28,0:23:57.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh no! It's out of lead!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.85,0:23:59.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, do you have a pen or anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.82,0:24:03.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a fountain pen in the desk, if that's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.16,0:24:07.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's strange.\NMy husband always had it in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.13,0:24:09.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even his trick color pens are gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.73,0:24:12.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How long're you gonna look at those numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.40,0:24:16.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The police are right. It was the daughter playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.37,0:24:19.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I took our daughter to the show that day,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.31,0:24:23.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so they assumed she entered those numbers before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.38,0:24:29.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning your husband didn't use the phone that day for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.52,0:24:30.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.52,0:24:36.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, the killer poisoned the victim before everyone left, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.42,0:24:42.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Probably using a capsule that dissolved during the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.90,0:24:47.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the victim was stuck in here the entire time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.17,0:24:51.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me, I think I'd try to leave a clue about who did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.14,0:24:55.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but I guess he couldn't! There were no pens in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.11,0:24:58.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All there was was this phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.11,0:25:03.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How dumb. If the victim used the phone,\Nhe would've called for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.28,0:25:07.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, huh? I doubt the phone was unplugged or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.32,0:25:09.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Unplugged?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.62,0:25:10.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.99,0:25:15.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer locked your husband in here after unplugging the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.56,0:25:19.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it was plugged back in during all the commotion later on!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.63,0:25:21.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.20,0:25:23.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All three suspects are magicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.94,0:25:27.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They could all pull off such a stealthy trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.78,0:25:31.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer also hid the phone with the cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.45,0:25:32.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When the body was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.75,0:25:37.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would be clear the phone was unplugged if someone tried to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.49,0:25:42.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And your husband, poisoned and locked inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.12,0:25:45.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,wanted to leave a clue about the person responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.36,0:25:49.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the pens were gone, and the phone unplugged.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.93,0:25:55.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only option left was to use the redial button to leave a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.20,0:26:00.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when unplugged, as long as there's power, numbers are saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.94,0:26:07.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, as a hint pointing to this, he left the two cards on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.82,0:26:10.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then my husband really did enter those numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.49,0:26:14.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He re-hid the phone under the cards
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.16,0:26:19.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because if someone used the phone later,\Nhis number would be erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.36,0:26:24.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, if the phone stood out too much,\Nthe killer might get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.77,0:26:28.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left is to decipher this strange number message, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.40,0:26:29.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's why I—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.64,0:26:32.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.44,0:26:35.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my pen! You wanted something to write with, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.74,0:26:37.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.01,0:26:40.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You realized something interesting again!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.72,0:26:42.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Think you could tell us about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.78,0:26:49.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's nothing much, but look at this first group of numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.62,0:26:54.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,1-2-6-8-7-1.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.26,0:26:57.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On its own, it doesn't make much sense,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.47,0:27:03.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but if you connect 1, 2, 6, 8, 7, and 1 on the phone pad,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.61,0:27:06.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you get a real strange shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.41,0:27:08.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.14,0:27:10.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the letter D!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.38,0:27:12.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! So that's called a "D"?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.71,0:27:18.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! Then the next one, 3-2-4-8-9 is C!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.45,0:27:25.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! These number sequences write out four characters!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.36,0:27:32.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Adding in the 1-3-5-4-8 and 1-3-9-7 should leave us
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.30,0:27:37.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with the message your husband left before he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.57,0:27:40.28,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"DCMAKO"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.24,0:27:40.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,DCMAKO?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.51,0:27:42.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,MAKO? Could that mean Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.78,0:27:44.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.58,0:27:46.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then she killed my husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.98,0:27:50.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. This isn't enough to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.02,0:27:54.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be a message he left for Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.02,0:27:57.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and we don't know what the "DC" before "MAKO" means...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.46,0:28:01.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really amazing to figure that out\Nfrom some weird numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.80,0:28:02.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really something!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.73,0:28:06.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. You're really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.80,0:28:09.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really something, Dad! You're so smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.37,0:28:12.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, this was a cinch for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.38,0:28:16.78,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.81,0:28:20.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what {\i1}is{\i0} this "DC"?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.82,0:28:25.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only DCs I know are\NDC Brand and Washington, DC...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.49,0:28:27.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct current...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.56,0:28:29.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Da capo!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.69,0:28:33.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the D.C. that's often in sheet music!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.39,0:28:35.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's read "da capo"!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.50,0:28:39.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, he did play the piano on occasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.63,0:28:42.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I think he often read sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.34,0:28:45.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, what does "da capo" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.44,0:28:48.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It means to go back to the start and repeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.44,0:28:50.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Repeat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.78,0:28:53.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} leave with your daughter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.92,0:28:55.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, to buy clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.92,0:28:58.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you contact her right away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.02,0:29:02.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I can. She has a pager.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.03,0:29:11.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's from your mom.\NShe must want us to hurry home.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.67,0:29:15.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? But I still want to stay with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.74,0:29:19.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, we're going somewhere really fun next, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.37,0:29:23.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'll take you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.01,0:29:26.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To an even more wonderful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.75,0:29:29.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} plans to...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.75,0:29:32.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She probably plans to kill your daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.72,0:29:35.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The "DC Mako" your husband left behind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.29,0:29:39.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,likely means that Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} intends to repeat her murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.23,0:29:40.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.30,0:29:43.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just call the other two pupils for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.63,0:29:46.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll all split up and search for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.91,0:29:56.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano! Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Where are you? Ayano!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.91,0:29:58.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.68,0:30:00.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.23,0:30:02.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.42,0:30:05.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No use...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.36,0:30:09.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Can't find her!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.72,0:30:10.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Any luck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.46,0:30:12.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Can't find them anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.46,0:30:15.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess we should ask the police to search now...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.46,0:30:18.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, why would Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} kill my husband?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.27,0:30:21.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She must have some connection with that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.37,0:30:27.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, the man with the black hat in that one photograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.04,0:30:29.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It {\i1}was{\i0} Yoshiro Kinoshita after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.54,0:30:33.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kinoshita? The genius magician\Nwho died 14 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.88,0:30:36.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "after all," Sanada{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.75,0:30:41.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw her when I went to the basement room one night.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.09,0:30:44.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mako was embracing a picture with care.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.69,0:30:49.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought something was up,\Nbut I never imagined she'd kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.36,0:30:52.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I'm pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.00,0:30:54.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I was flustered when we found the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.70,0:31:00.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I never saw Mako cut the string on his rings or plug the phone back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.11,0:31:01.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.91,0:31:06.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been found out?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.58,0:31:07.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.98,0:31:09.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.78,0:31:10.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayano!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.50,0:31:13.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. She's just asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.22,0:31:19.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was actually going to put her to sleep for a very long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.36,0:31:21.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,just like my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.50,0:31:22.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.66,0:31:26.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The Yoshiro Kinoshita you were just talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.80,0:31:29.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was my brother, 14 years older than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.60,0:31:35.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At only 20, he had received every accolade a magician could obtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.41,0:31:42.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And he was my only family, after our parents died when I was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.15,0:31:47.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then that man destroyed my brother like a bug!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.09,0:31:51.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Motoyasu Tsukumo was jealous of his talent!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.43,0:31:54.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious! My husband would never...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.20,0:31:57.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a lie. I saw it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.43,0:32:01.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,On that day, 14 years ago,\Nhe fiddled with the handcuffs
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.44,0:32:03.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that my brother used in shows.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.84,0:32:08.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Immediately after, my brother drowned in the practice water{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} tan{\r}k,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.08,0:32:10.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because his handcuffs wouldn't come off.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.98,0:32:18.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The incident was swept under the rug as an accident, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.79,0:32:24.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So you became his pupil\Nto avenge your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.66,0:32:28.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. My last name was{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ged when I was taken in by relatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.86,0:32:32.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so he probably never realized.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.03,0:32:36.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother was killed right on my 7th birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.34,0:32:40.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The birthday when I was left all alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.07,0:32:46.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I killed him just before his daughter turned 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.18,0:32:49.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I revealed my identity to him after I administered the poison,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.32,0:32:55.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he still seemed calm,\Nso I threatened to kill his daughter, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.49,0:32:58.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He suddenly lost his calm and...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.66,0:33:04.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! That was the only way to protect my status!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.37,0:33:08.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can have my life.\NJust keep my daughter out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.30,0:33:13.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I said, I planned to kill his daughter,\Nbut then I decided not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.21,0:33:16.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She did nothing wrong, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.91,0:33:19.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, he was a foolish man.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.41,0:33:25.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He naively let me tie his rings together\Nto show me a new trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.85,0:33:29.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he unwittingly swallowed my poison capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.86,0:33:33.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For Japan's greatest magician, that's a real laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.63,0:33:35.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true, Mako.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.76,0:33:41.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He knew you were going to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.17,0:33:43.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.70,0:33:48.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you. I saw you hugging the photo of your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.64,0:33:51.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our teacher had been with me then.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.65,0:33:58.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he said, "Don't tell this to anyone until the time comes."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.29,0:34:03.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you won, Mako. Your trick completely fooled the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.72,0:34:10.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the dying message he left\Nwon't stand as evidence at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.67,0:34:16.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ridicule me. I have no intention of taking the stage now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.37,0:34:21.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go to the police and lower my own curtain on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.14,0:34:27.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, it wasn't right for me to make Ayano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} share my lot in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.35,0:34:34.72,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Afterward, we took Mako{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} to the police
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.72,0:34:39.49,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and were supposed to return to the detective agency for a late dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.13,0:34:44.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, it's already after 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.20,0:34:46.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.44,0:34:54.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! I forgot to buy ingredients for dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.48,0:34:58.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and I'll get something at the convenience store!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.95,0:35:02.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take too long. I'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.75,0:35:09.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Say, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}. This isn't the way to the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.09,0:35:13.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're lost, we should go back to the detective agency first.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.79,0:35:16.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We have to go back...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.19,0:35:27.46,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kudo"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.97,0:35:19.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to your house!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.37,0:35:27.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about? This is Shin'ichi-{\i1}niichan{\i0}'s house!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.68,0:35:30.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.04,0:35:36.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So, that's how you've tricked us all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.05,0:35:38.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.69,0:35:40.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin'ichi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.16,0:35:50.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Shin'ichi, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.20,0:35:57.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you saying?\NOf course I'm not Shin'ichi-{\i1}niichan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.14,0:35:59.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.18,0:36:04.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That reasoning, ability to take action,\Nand lack of musical knowledge!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.25,0:36:05.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're exactly alike!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.95,0:36:08.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, look closely! I'm a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.98,0:36:12.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You probably took a weird drug Dr. Agasa made or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.86,0:36:15.99,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Everything's really adding up!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.99,0:36:23.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit playing dumb already!\NI have so, so much to say to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.70,0:36:26.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Not good...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.80,0:36:29.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.17,0:36:32.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say crazy things if you don't have proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.54,0:36:35.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's proof right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.15,0:36:43.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There! I've never seen such a close look-alike before!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.35,0:36:44.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.89,0:36:48.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to fess up, Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.09,0:36:49.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.43,0:36:56.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you in front of our home so late at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.23,0:37:01.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s mother...\NWhen did you return from LA?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.64,0:37:04.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just now. I took the last flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.31,0:37:06.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Some things came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.98,0:37:11.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh no! If Mom blurts out too much now...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.85,0:37:14.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.18,0:37:18.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing. Let's have your birth mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.66,0:37:22.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,tell us who you really are!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.33,0:37:28.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.76,0:37:32.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! It's good to see you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.13,0:37:34.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.44,0:37:35.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.17,0:37:40.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my grandfather's brother's daughter's cousin's uncle's grandson!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.74,0:37:44.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he says he's a relative of Dr. Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.21,0:37:48.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! He and I are very distant relatives!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.35,0:37:52.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't he look too much like Shin'ichi when he was little?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.22,0:37:56.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You think? Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} seems much nicer to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.66,0:37:59.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom's name is Fumiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.26,0:38:00.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.00,0:38:03.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.83,0:38:10.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too odd for a grade-schooler\Nto be so good at figuring things out!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.44,0:38:14.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-He must've picked up some of Shin'ichi's qualities!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.04,0:38:16.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He used to visit all the time, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.38,0:38:18.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He used to hang out with Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.65,0:38:19.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.52,0:38:22.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I love Shin'ichi-{\i1}niichan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.18,0:38:24.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.65,0:38:30.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. Think about it.\NWould Shin'ichi do something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.79,0:38:33.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're scary, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.93,0:38:37.30,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You're scary, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.91,0:38:48.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! I guess I had the wrong idea, again!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.28,0:38:51.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget everything I just said!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.45,0:38:53.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you a yummy Salisbury steak as an apology!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.68,0:38:54.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.25,0:38:55.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.85,0:38:58.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could I take him for two or three days?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.95,0:39:03.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My vacation starts tomorrow,\Nand we haven't talked in so long!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.49,0:39:08.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that should be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.13,0:39:10.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see you later, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.97,0:39:12.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.97,0:39:14.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.75,0:39:16.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.41,0:39:24.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, why are you back?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.31,0:39:28.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me your fight with Dad this afternoon is the reason why.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.12,0:39:31.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's some way to talk to the person who saved your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.59,0:39:33.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Saved my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.12,0:39:35.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Dr. Agasa
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.92,0:39:38.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that you took baths with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.56,0:39:40.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't covered for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.10,0:39:43.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who knows what her karate would've done to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.07,0:39:48.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.01,0:39:54.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, I hope you told Dad\Nyou were coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.98,0:39:56.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.78,0:39:58.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.08,0:40:02.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright! I'm going to live with you for a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.22,0:40:04.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez! Don't get me involved, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.75,0:40:11.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But whenever I'm with mini-you,\NI feel young again, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.80,0:40:21.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's have din-din with Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.64,0:40:23.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.95,0:40:41.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.02,0:40:43.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, are you awake, Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.95,0:40:45.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.39,0:40:49.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I also came back to Japan\Nto take care of something out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.23,0:40:50.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.96,0:40:52.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.57,0:40:59.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.91,0:41:03.71,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi Yabu'uchi (37)\NYukiko's old classmate
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.40,0:41:03.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You came! Thank you! I know you must be busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.17,0:41:06.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd rush here from the other side of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.84,0:41:09.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to help my childhood friend, Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.35,0:41:11.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Where are Yusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.88,0:41:18.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, those two are busy. But don't worry! I brought him instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.42,0:41:20.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Don't tell me he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.42,0:41:24.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! My second son, Conan! I had him in Los Angeles!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.53,0:41:25.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.53,0:41:28.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a kid, but he's quite sharp!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.27,0:41:32.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You and your husband must be getting along well!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.00,0:41:33.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.51,0:41:39.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what is it you want us to look into?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.58,0:41:41.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.58,0:41:44.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Guests, Hiromi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.48,0:41:46.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Yoshifusa!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.82,0:41:50.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Yukiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! She used to visit all the time when she was little!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.79,0:41:52.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good to see you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.97,0:41:58.72,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshifusa Yabu'uchi (64)\NHiromi's uncle
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.99,0:41:59.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, I don't remember her.\NBut I {\i1}did{\i0} live in Brazil for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.90,0:42:04.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Make yourselves at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.47,0:42:06.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's go, Carlos!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.69,0:42:09.27,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Carlos (26)\NYoshifusa Yabu'uchi's friend
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.64,0:42:12.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Carlos?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.38,0:42:16.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Yoshifusa says he's a friend he brought back from Brazil...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.78,0:42:18.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.45,0:42:22.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me. How does Uncle Yoshifusa seem to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.09,0:42:22.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.89,0:42:25.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like his face, voice, and feel...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.92,0:42:30.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm. We used to play with him a lot,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.66,0:42:34.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he went to Brazil before I entered grade school, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.43,0:42:38.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it Uncle Yoshifusa who you wanted us to investigate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.14,0:42:41.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. He returned from Brazil three days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.94,0:42:46.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he seems different from before...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.04,0:42:52.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not show him to your dad? He's your dad's little brother, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.38,0:42:54.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.89,0:42:59.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My father, Yoshichika, died last month of cancer...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.96,0:43:01.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Cancer?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.56,0:43:04.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. My mother passed away 15 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.83,0:43:09.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and all of Uncle Yoshifusa's friends died early on...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.60,0:43:15.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, we're the only two who've met him on numerous occasions.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.11,0:43:18.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, why are you so suspicious of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.24,0:43:19.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.20,0:43:21.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.01,0:43:29.02,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Hidekazu Yabu'uchi (41)\NHiromi's husband (married into family)
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.08,0:43:26.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone suspects that old man\Nmight be an impostor
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.92,0:43:29.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,trying to take her father's inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.55,0:43:34.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He owned all the land in this area,\Nand his inheritance is worth a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.99,0:43:39.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The lawyer says he left a will,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.03,0:43:47.08,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,0)}"Will"
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.70,0:43:47.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and that anyone who's absent when it's read doesn't get a single yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.80,0:43:51.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When is it going to be read?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.28,0:43:54.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow night at 10:00, when his mourning ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.14,0:43:58.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means we gotta unmask that old man before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.25,0:43:58.38,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshiyuki Yabu'uchi (32)\NHiromi's younger brother
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.76,0:43:59.09,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(325,0)\move(512,336,484,336)}Keiko Yabu'uchi (28)\NYoshiyuki's wife
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.09,0:44:02.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Keiko Yabu'uchi (28)\NYoshiyuki's wife
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.05,0:44:09.73,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Machiko Yabu'uchi (39)\NYoshichika's 2nd wife
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.18,0:44:02.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or else we'll end up with a smaller share.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.49,0:44:06.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It might not just mean a smaller share.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.02,0:44:10.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on the contents of the will, we may get nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.03,0:44:14.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyways, we gotta do something before tomorrow night.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.03,0:44:17.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Where did all these people come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.54,0:44:21.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.71,0:44:24.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't there {\i1}any{\i0} old photos left?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.71,0:44:30.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems Uncle Yoshifusa took them all when he went to Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.58,0:44:37.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, could this be him?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.02,0:44:39.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? You guys are in it too, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.72,0:44:41.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.53,0:44:45.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's him! The one in the middle!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.00,0:44:47.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's definitely Uncle Yoshifusa!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.43,0:44:51.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he's too young in it to be of any use.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.00,0:44:53.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, he has a hat on.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.84,0:44:55.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But this brings back memories!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.67,0:44:59.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is from the city baseball tournament!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.21,0:45:04.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember? A runner's shoe spike injured his leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.95,0:45:09.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. He had to get lots of stitches at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.49,0:45:12.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, shouldn't he still have that scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.46,0:45:13.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.96,0:45:17.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi! Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.06,0:45:17.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.36,0:45:21.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle! Would you like some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.90,0:45:23.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.87,0:45:25.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.89,0:45:28.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I'll clean it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.51,0:45:29.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not there!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.91,0:45:31.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The scar isn't there!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.31,0:45:32.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.21,0:45:33.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.98,0:45:37.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, do you mean this?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.48,0:45:44.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A runner spiked my leg hard on first base
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.19,0:45:48.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,during a baseball game 30 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.23,0:45:51.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? He {\i1}does{\i0} have a scar...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.43,0:45:54.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning it's really him?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.10,0:45:56.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, you did suspect me!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.70,0:46:00.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother was right! There are no decent people here!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.50,0:46:02.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wise to bring Carlos with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.94,0:46:04.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wise?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.21,0:46:08.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a bodyguard I hired in Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.01,0:46:10.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Bodyguard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.48,0:46:12.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you need one?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.55,0:46:18.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd hire one too, if you got a letter like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.42,0:46:20.19,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}"There's no inheritance for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.19,0:46:22.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If you value your life, don't come back."
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.69,0:46:24.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Life?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.04,0:46:41.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get this letter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.04,0:46:46.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One month ago. It was sent to my house in Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.04,0:46:50.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It goes without saying that the sender's name was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.62,0:46:55.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't care about my brother's inheritance, but I did want to see
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.75,0:47:00.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the faces of the buffoons who would send such a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.73,0:47:02.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Buffoons?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.59,0:47:06.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if you're finished here, then get the hell out!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.00,0:47:09.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, mister! Teach me some {\i1}kanji{\i0} letters!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.47,0:47:12.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom won't help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.37,0:47:13.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Shin...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.87,0:47:15.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.87,0:47:19.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you write "happy new year"?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.08,0:47:23.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Left-handed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.72,0:47:28.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see that, Sis?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.02,0:47:32.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But I can't remember if our uncle was left-handed or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.49,0:47:34.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember, Yuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.29,0:47:35.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.89,0:47:42.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he did have the scar on his leg, so I think he {\i1}is{\i0} Uncle Yoshifusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.90,0:47:45.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he could've heard from someone
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.37,0:47:50.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and relied on an old scar of his own he just happened to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.51,0:47:52.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that geezer {\i1}is{\i0} a fake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.68,0:47:55.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he's the real deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.45,0:47:59.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at the photo of Uncle Yoshifusa we found in the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.62,0:48:06.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? He has a mitt on his right hand.\NProof that he's left-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.16,0:48:07.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.26,0:48:09.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, his handwriting is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.55,0:48:10.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Handwriting?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.26,0:48:21.94,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Happy New Year"
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.10,0:48:13.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I found this postcard with the photograph!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.83,0:48:18.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A New Year's card that Uncle Yoshifusa sent when he was in Brazil!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.70,0:48:22.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? The handwriting matches exactly with what he wrote just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.47,0:48:27.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on. Don't tell me you had him write this so you could check?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.41,0:48:30.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what I'd expect from the son of Yusaku Kudo,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.15,0:48:32.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the world-renowned mystery writer!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.82,0:48:38.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my son! Mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.22,0:48:39.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.66,0:48:43.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.73,0:48:47.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The old well is still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.37,0:48:49.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after that accident...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.23,0:48:50.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.27,0:48:51.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.70,0:48:54.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mother fell into it and died.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.67,0:49:01.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She disappeared one day 15 years ago,\Nafter a very heavy snowfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.11,0:49:03.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We all looked for her, but couldn't find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.51,0:49:06.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The next morning, just when we were about to contact the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.55,0:49:11.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we found her in the well, dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.26,0:49:13.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were going to destroy the well because it was dangerous,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.96,0:49:21.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but Father asked to keep it until he died too, so he'd never forget her.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.20,0:49:24.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's why there's a fence around the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.57,0:49:29.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I went and put it there myself, so nobody else'd fall in.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.57,0:49:33.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the real trouble was during the funeral before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.78,0:49:34.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Funeral?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.91,0:49:38.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mom's brother suddenly caused a scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.42,0:49:42.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Claimed one of us knocked her down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.42,0:49:45.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What really did happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.02,0:49:49.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cause was that camellia plant our uncle grew
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.03,0:49:52.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as a wedding gift for our parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.53,0:49:54.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Camellia?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.03,0:49:56.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}sasanqua{\i0} next to the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.60,0:50:02.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Our mother stood on the edge of the well to pick a flower, but slipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.24,0:50:07.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted to show it to us.\NShe loved those flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.78,0:50:11.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They hardly bloomed during the winter of that year,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.72,0:50:15.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and she had been waiting for them eagerly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.82,0:50:20.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A camellia flower was found in her hand, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.99,0:50:27.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, in the end, her brother didn't seem to accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.83,0:50:30.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Where is he now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.74,0:50:31.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.84,0:50:36.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was rather old back then, so perhaps he's passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.84,0:50:41.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! If he's still alive,\Nwon't he get the inheritance, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.31,0:50:45.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! Legally, he shouldn't have any inheritance rights to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.42,0:50:47.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not necessarily true.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.82,0:50:54.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He could still receive some inheritance,\Nif it's in my husband's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.03,0:50:59.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what, he might show up before 10:00 tomorrow night,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.26,0:51:01.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when the will is read?!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.23,0:51:02.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.63,0:51:07.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. If he's alive,\Nhe'll be absolutely sure to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.77,0:51:12.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, he seems to have a 15-year old grudge with you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.38,0:51:16.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, it has nothing to do with me, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.91,0:51:21.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,as I wasn't a part of this family when she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.92,0:51:26.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes! I'm off to a friend's after-wedding party now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.62,0:51:30.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I leave the rest to you, Hiromi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.36,0:51:32.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.00,0:51:36.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.80,0:51:38.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.74,0:51:41.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was just there!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.34,0:51:45.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A strange person watching us from behind that wood gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.81,0:51:50.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.41,0:51:53.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure you weren't just seeing things, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.42,0:51:57.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. I'm pretty sure someone was here...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.69,0:52:05.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like this. Don't tell me this person is actually her brother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.93,0:52:11.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to bother you by staying here and having you make such a nice meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.44,0:52:15.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no problem! {\i1}Nabe{\i0} dishes are more fun with lots of people!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.84,0:52:19.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. You even packed a{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ge of clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.58,0:52:23.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you were planning to stay from the start...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.28,0:52:26.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that? Did you say something, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.88,0:52:29.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.35,0:52:33.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could that be at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.06,0:52:34.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.89,0:52:36.23,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, Hiromi{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-san{\r\be10}?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.23,0:52:39.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mother! What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.36,0:52:42.60,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That reminds me, we were out of firewood for the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.60,0:52:45.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. So I thought we'd go without using the bath tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.14,0:52:48.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.47,0:52:52.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! Let's drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.74,0:52:56.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit it! I'm on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.38,0:52:57.52,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.52,0:53:01.82,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I bought firewood for the bath this morning and put it by the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.82,0:53:02.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.49,0:53:05.42,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Well, see you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.42,0:53:08.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother seems to be quite drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.26,0:53:11.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She sure is carefree in the middle of Dad's mourning.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.00,0:53:18.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! A {\i1}nabe{\i0} for dinner tonight!\NNow I can rest easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.00,0:53:19.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Rest easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.30,0:53:24.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't have to ask Carlos\Nto taste-test my food for poison!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.11,0:53:25.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.84,0:53:29.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that letter was a prank or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.95,0:53:31.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.39,0:53:37.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How's the water, Yuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.82,0:53:39.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems just right!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.99,0:53:43.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, a caldron bath in these times?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.49,0:53:46.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what's wrong with that? It has elegance.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.40,0:53:50.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. Want to bathe together like in the old days?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.94,0:53:52.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.40,0:53:56.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Could you tell Uncle the bath is ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.14,0:53:59.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, he did love baths!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.01,0:54:01.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He always took the first bath, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.08,0:54:06.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think he and that Carlos person will fit in this small bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.08,0:54:07.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.59,0:54:10.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle has taken a bath every day since he's come here,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.52,0:54:12.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but Carlos always stayed in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.86,0:54:16.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? He would take a bath all alone, leaving his bodyguard behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.23,0:54:25.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now I see. Carlos watches everyone while he's in the bath...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.20,0:54:28.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. I'm counting on you, Carlos.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.54,0:54:35.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.18,0:54:37.72,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Well? Did you find the firewood?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.72,0:54:40.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Uncle just went to take a bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.92,0:54:42.32,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.32,0:54:46.96,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm still at the party. I don't think I'll be back until after 11:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.96,0:54:50.53,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm sorry to ask, but could you keep the bath warm until then?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.53,0:54:52.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.67,0:54:59.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a great bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.27,0:55:01.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Think I'll go next.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.64,0:55:03.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll go after you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.68,0:55:09.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! How was the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.88,0:55:12.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a little cold, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.55,0:55:15.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I better rebuild the fire then.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.10,0:55:16.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.22,0:55:17.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the hard work!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.36,0:55:18.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Make yourself at home!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.09,0:55:27.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly! You can take baths with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, but not with me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.84,0:55:35.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Hiromi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.44,0:55:40.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,J-Just now! There was a weird man with sunglasses behind the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.84,0:55:43.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So, I {\i1}did{\i0} see that guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.62,0:55:49.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Doesn't that pail seem strange?!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.25,0:55:50.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.12,0:55:52.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See?! The well bucket is up!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.39,0:55:57.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like something's stuck to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.66,0:55:59.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's pull it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.13,0:56:02.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty heavy!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.54,0:56:07.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Heave-ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.25,0:56:19.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.65,0:56:24.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How did this happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.86,0:56:27.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me she jumped into the well to commit suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.66,0:56:34.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! There's a stab mark in her chest!\NThis is how she died!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.30,0:56:36.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.30,0:56:39.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean someone here did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.24,0:56:40.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.97,0:56:45.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s last phone call\Nwas at around 9:00, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.98,0:56:49.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. From the banquet hall of the hotel near the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.65,0:56:52.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I went into the bath 10 minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.72,0:56:57.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone leave the room while I was in the bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.59,0:57:00.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No one.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.02,0:57:03.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it couldn't have been someone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.66,0:57:07.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would take at least one hour\Nby car from the hotel to this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.87,0:57:09.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, while I was in the bath,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.93,0:57:15.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she returned, and someone killed her\Nand threw her down the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.51,0:57:18.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Though, it's a different story if you suspect me,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.28,0:57:20.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,even though I met her for the first time today.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.61,0:57:23.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then who {\i1}did{\i0} kill her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.15,0:57:26.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be the suspicious man with sunglasses you just saw?!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.48,0:57:29.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would he kill Mother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.59,0:57:33.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something in her pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.49,0:57:34.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.89,0:57:36.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.73,0:57:38.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,a camellia flower!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.16,0:57:43.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then... Then the person I just saw r-really was...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.77,0:57:47.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The man from 15 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.36,0:57:56.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The deceased is Machiko Yabu'uchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 39.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.43,0:57:59.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure she's the second wife of Yoshichika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.44,0:58:02.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the head of this house who died last month?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.67,0:58:04.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.27,0:58:05.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.94,0:58:08.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't found the murder weapon yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.04,0:58:13.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but it appears she died of blood loss\Nfrom the stab to the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.02,0:58:15.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.66,0:58:20.16,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.98,0:58:20.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we say the body was found just after 10:00 pm?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.92,0:58:22.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.16,0:58:27.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed odd that the well bucket was up,\Nso when we pulled it up...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.13,0:58:29.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we found her body in the well.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.93,0:58:35.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.64,0:58:40.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! I just got chills when I imagined it...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.58,0:58:46.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, this would mean that the killer was one of you eight
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.58,0:58:49.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who were here when it happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.42,0:58:52.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.02,0:58:57.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was at a friend's after-wedding party at the hotel by the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.86,0:59:02.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and she called from there at around 9:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.93,0:59:06.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she left by car right after calling,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.33,0:59:08.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she wouldn't be back until after 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.84,0:59:10.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all in the same room
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.17,0:59:13.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,between 10:00 and the time the body was found,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.58,0:59:15.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we couldn't have killed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.91,0:59:22.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! I was the only one not with them,\Nbecause I was in the bath!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.38,0:59:26.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! T-Then {\i1}you're{\i0} the killer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.02,0:59:31.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! I only met the late Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} today!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.79,0:59:33.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.31,0:59:34.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.43,0:59:38.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth! Yukiko's been living abroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.07,0:59:42.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just happened to ask her here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.17,0:59:46.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yukiko"? Oh, wait a minute! Don't tell me you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.64,0:59:49.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yukiko Fujimine{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the actress?!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.61,0:59:50.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.61,0:59:53.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.01,0:59:59.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to watch you every week on "Dangerous Policewoman Story!"
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.05,1:00:02.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You actually inspired me to join the police!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.09,1:00:03.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.93,1:00:05.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That makes you even more suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.59,1:00:06.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.96,1:00:11.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you're skilled at using guns and knives.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.27,1:00:13.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was just a TV show!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.57,1:00:16.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Are we gonna be alright with this cop?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.81,1:00:20.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Was it really Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who called?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.78,1:00:22.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It was her.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.78,1:00:28.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She responded to the conversation,\Nand I could hear the party, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.35,1:00:32.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See?! Only you could've done it!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.39,1:00:33.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.92,1:00:37.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's someone else who's suspicious!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.89,1:00:40.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He was lurking around here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.33,1:00:45.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A strange person covering his face with sunglasses, a hat, and a scarf.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.17,1:00:47.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A s-strange person?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.30,1:00:51.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it's the brother of our mom, who died 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.77,1:00:57.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She tried to pick a flower there and accidentally fell into the well.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.18,1:01:01.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he's convinced one of us pushed her down there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.19,1:01:10.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But just like me, Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wasn't part of the family 15 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.39,1:01:12.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So why would he kill her?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.29,1:01:13.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.96,1:01:17.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was dark back here. Maybe he mistook her for someone else?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.97,1:01:22.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, it's still not certain if he {\i1}was{\i0} the man with sunglasses...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.64,1:01:25.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.64,1:01:28.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Here's this camellia flower.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.98,1:01:30.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A flower from that tree?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.65,1:01:35.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This was in this lady's breast pocket.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.22,1:01:40.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you freakin' out for?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.79,1:01:43.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're with the homicide department, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.86,1:01:48.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Actually, this is my first real investigation...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.86,1:01:51.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a cold going around the department,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.37,1:01:54.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I was the only one they could send...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.27,1:01:56.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, I'm not good around dead bodies...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.81,1:01:59.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,- Oh. I see.\N- Oh. I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.17,1:02:03.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Anyways, to find out the precise time the victim returned home,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.18,1:02:06.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll need to check with the taxi\Nshe took from the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.88,1:02:07.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Taxi?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.85,1:02:11.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother took the family car.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.52,1:02:12.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Car?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.95,1:02:15.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The car's in the yard, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.96,1:02:18.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. I didn't see one anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.93,1:02:22.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The car isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.36,1:02:25.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How strange. It's always parked here.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.97,1:02:28.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where could Mother have put the car?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.70,1:02:31.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She had been drinking at the party,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.57,1:02:35.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so perhaps she left the car there\Nand took a taxi home?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.08,1:02:35.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.94,1:02:37.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.45,1:02:38.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.55,1:02:42.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found a car in the woods right behind the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.48,1:02:44.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-In the woods?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.42,1:02:47.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's a car doing there?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.16,1:02:57.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is our car! But why is it in the woods?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.67,1:03:02.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the killer planned to use it,\Nbut{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ged his mind?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.94,1:03:08.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mother probably just\Nran out of gas or had engine trouble!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.88,1:03:14.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So she walked to the house,\Nwhere that man was waiting to stab her!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.75,1:03:21.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange. The engine works just fine,\Nand the key was still in.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.56,1:03:25.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, it still has gas, and doesn't seem to have any flat tires...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.49,1:03:29.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And this empty cassette case seems curious.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.53,1:03:31.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see its contents anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.97,1:03:36.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only a cell phone in the glove compartment.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.04,1:03:38.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.34,1:03:45.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, you'll all sleep tonight while we keep watch.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.51,1:03:49.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, that man could still be out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.65,1:03:56.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez. We all gotta sleep in the same room as some cops?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.73,1:03:58.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This sucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.59,1:04:01.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.93,1:04:04.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How much have you figured out?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.63,1:04:06.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.50,1:04:08.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, tell me!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.00,1:04:12.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get accused of being the killer\Nif we leave it to that lamebrain cop!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.47,1:04:15.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are still too many mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.08,1:04:21.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's that man in the sunglasses,\Nthe car left in the woods,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.08,1:04:23.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the empty cassette case.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.28,1:04:28.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's most curious of all is the body\Nthat was tied to the well rope.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.29,1:04:35.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it was hidden in the well,\Nit almost asked to be found.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.16,1:04:40.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There are too many mysteries scattered about.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.64,1:04:42.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.60,1:04:45.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that storeroom open before?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.07,1:04:45.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.12,1:04:57.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.72,1:05:00.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.16,1:05:06.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Let's get back to our room and sleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.19,1:05:07.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up, Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.74,1:05:20.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.74,1:05:24.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.25,1:05:29.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found the murder weapon in the well!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.18,1:05:30.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.75,1:05:34.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A kitchen knife, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.36,1:05:37.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please see if it matches with the victim's stab wound.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.76,1:05:38.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.76,1:05:40.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that plastic thing?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.90,1:05:43.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's a woman's raincoat.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.90,1:05:46.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The knife was wrapped in it for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.63,1:05:47.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A raincoat?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.84,1:05:52.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, forget it! Authorized personnel only!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.37,1:05:53.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.91,1:05:55.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This person just barged in...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.64,1:05:58.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I'm the attorney!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.18,1:05:59.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Attorney?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.16,1:06:04.67,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,The Yabu'uchi Family Attorney
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.78,1:06:04.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to read the will of the late Yoshichika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.67,1:06:06.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.96,1:06:09.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's finally time...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.86,1:06:13.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! Delay the reading of the will?!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.26,1:06:16.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The killer still hasn't been caught,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.53,1:06:18.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and we haven't finished checking the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.63,1:06:20.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reading should be moved to a later date...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.80,1:06:22.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Screw that!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.30,1:06:25.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the right to decide that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.87,1:06:28.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The greedier you are, the more noise you make.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.74,1:06:30.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.88,1:06:34.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geezer! Don't be rude with me!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.08,1:06:38.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You got that?! You're just an impostor, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.69,1:06:41.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is pain the only way to get through to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.23,1:06:50.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on, you two!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.90,1:06:57.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How about this? We police will also attend the reading. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.04,1:06:59.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's all be friends!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.84,1:07:01.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-That was...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.94,1:07:04.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Brazilian jiu-jutsu.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.08,1:07:06.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's quite skilled, at that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.92,1:07:11.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean Carlos is even more skilled than him?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.99,1:07:17.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, if he's so good at self-defense, why would he hire a bodyguard?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.39,1:07:21.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good question. Maybe he's just being extra cautious.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.81,1:07:36.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reading of Yoshichika Yabu'uchi's last will will now take place.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.38,1:07:38.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I ask that you listen quietly.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.49,1:07:45.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.42,1:07:50.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What is it? What is that sound?!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.09,1:07:54.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with the tape recorder?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.93,1:08:02.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshichika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} recorded a tape that accompanies his written will.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.21,1:08:08.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I don't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.78,1:08:11.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, isn't that the record button?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.78,1:08:14.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to stop it!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.45,1:08:20.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Duck!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.46,1:08:23.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look out!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.79,1:08:26.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.26,1:08:33.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The cabinet! An arrow came out of that cabinet!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.84,1:08:36.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.81,1:08:39.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.48,1:08:42.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A c-crossbow!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.51,1:08:46.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And this clock...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.62,1:08:49.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A timing device...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.58,1:08:53.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, it was set to fire at a specified time...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.16,1:08:57.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who would do this?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.23,1:08:59.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who set this up?!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.23,1:09:09.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who set this up?!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.10,1:09:11.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been that person who ran from the gate last night!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.73,1:09:16.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming he really is the brother of our mom who died 15 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.00,1:09:23.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...and that he held a grudge against our Yabu'uchi family...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.74,1:09:25.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.85,1:09:29.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He used the fact we would gather in here for the reading of the will
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.75,1:09:33.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and set up the crossbow and arrow there.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.32,1:09:36.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean anyone would've done, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.52,1:09:39.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it doesn't look that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.73,1:09:41.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.09,1:09:44.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Look at the room on the other side of the wall it went through.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.90,1:09:48.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See all the arrow holes in the floor mat?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.87,1:09:54.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's proof that the killer had done some test shots beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.21,1:09:57.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to hit the person sitting in that spot.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.65,1:10:01.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was decided from the start
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.92,1:10:05.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that the will would be read in that room, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.32,1:10:07.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.62,1:10:10.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's even more evidence, then.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.02,1:10:14.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, kid, there'd be no way to tell who'd sit where.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.46,1:10:16.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, there would.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.90,1:10:24.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The arrow flew at the "head seat," the one furthest from the exit,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.84,1:10:27.51,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Entrance
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.09,1:10:27.51,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Seats of\NHonor
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.09,1:10:27.51,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Humble\NSeats
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.14,1:10:27.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where the most senior person sits, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.97,1:10:32.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, that means the person who set up the arrow...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.48,1:10:36.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,had tried to target you, Uncle Yoshifusa.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.95,1:10:44.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, there's still another cretin out to take my life. Heaven help me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.19,1:10:46.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, isn't this a possibility?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.79,1:10:50.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if Uncle was the one who set up the arrow?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.90,1:10:58.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so. He barely dodged it after reacting to Conan's voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.31,1:10:59.86,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Duck!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.81,1:11:06.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, is all of this the doing of that strange man with the sunglasses?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.75,1:11:10.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's a very good possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.82,1:11:15.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... I'm sorry to interrupt...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.02,1:11:19.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But shouldn't we stop that tape recorder?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.09,1:11:22.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! I left it on record!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.66,1:11:27.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Did all of our dad's will get erased?!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.33,1:11:28.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.56,1:11:30.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, whoops!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.00,1:11:33.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I accidentally put it on Side B instead of Side A.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.37,1:11:37.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Side B was recorded to!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.11,1:11:41.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The will is safe and sound on Side A!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.15,1:11:42.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.88,1:11:45.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Just let us hear the will already!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.32,1:11:48.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please calm down. I'm rewinding it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.92,1:11:52.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I don't think we'll be able to solve this case
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.59,1:11:54.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,until we learn who that strange person is...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.59,1:11:59.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. But I have a good idea\Nwho set up the arrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.47,1:12:01.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's that person.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.30,1:12:05.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me they're in this room?!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.17,1:12:06.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.41,1:12:09.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon! Who is it?! Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.64,1:12:15.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No! There are still too many mysteries! I can't say anything rashly!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.12,1:12:16.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a hint, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.44,1:12:17.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.82,1:12:20.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.65,1:12:24.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, then! I'll figure it out on my own! Who needs you?!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.89,1:12:27.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! Don't pout, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.66,1:12:31.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Yamamura!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.30,1:12:35.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found a suspicious cassette tape by the bath stove!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.70,1:12:37.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A tape?!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.64,1:12:44.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, everyone! Please stay in this room until I return!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.14,1:12:47.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Huh? Where's Yukiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and that boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.28,1:12:49.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They just went outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.00,1:12:50.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.85,1:12:55.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, hold on! Please don't wander around on your own!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.32,1:12:58.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, where was this tape?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.33,1:13:01.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes. It was between the firewood.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.06,1:13:02.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.13,1:13:06.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromi got the bath ready, but she didn't say anything about a tape.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.80,1:13:11.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and we just received word from the examiners. It's strange...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.34,1:13:13.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.11,1:13:19.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the victim's fingerprints and blood were on the murder weapon,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.91,1:13:26.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but oddly enough, it appears she had held it as you would a sword.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.95,1:13:28.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A s-sword?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.64,1:13:29.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.86,1:13:31.99,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That {\i1}is{\i0} strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.99,1:13:35.26,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If she had grabbed the handle after being stabbed,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.26,1:13:37.83,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}it would've been upside-down.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.83,1:13:42.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If it was placed in her hands to make it look like a suicide,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.04,1:13:44.17,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}it would've made sense to have it upside down, too!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.17,1:13:51.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and I contacted the hotel the victim had supposedly been at.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.04,1:13:52.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did they say?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.78,1:13:58.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems she had indeed been there, but they're not sure when she left.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.12,1:14:02.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Hiromi did say something strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.09,1:14:08.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The late Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said she'd be home after 11:00,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.36,1:14:12.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so why was she back just after 10:00?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.43,1:14:13.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.87,1:14:20.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This door will take you straight from the bath to the stove.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.54,1:14:25.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And this stove is right next to the well, where the body was hidden!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.78,1:14:29.72,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Which means that tape...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.72,1:14:31.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.55,1:14:34.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear what's on the tape for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.49,1:14:43.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.63,1:14:44.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.36,1:14:50.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that sunglasses person was watching from this gate, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.24,1:14:54.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Hiromi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw him run from there, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.05,1:15:03.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it? Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.78,1:15:06.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.42,1:15:09.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry! Please return to the room!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.42,1:15:13.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Let's go listen to that tapey-wapey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.66,1:15:15.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit talking like that!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.10,1:15:19.40,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Machiko{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-chan{\r\be10}! Let's drink!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.40,1:15:22.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is from the party Mother was at!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.77,1:15:25.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This tape was really right next to the stove?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.47,1:15:26.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.81,1:15:32.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just as I thought! This makes all of Machiko{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s strange actions fit!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.95,1:15:39.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And her killer was the one\Nwho blurted out something odd!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.62,1:15:43.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mom. I'm gonna need your help.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.02,1:15:45.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured out who's responsible.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.83,1:15:50.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to explain using your voice,\Nso go along with it...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.83,1:15:52.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.50,1:15:53.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.23,1:15:56.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give me that. You wouldn't tell me anything earlier.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.84,1:16:01.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanna do it, do it on your own.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.07,1:16:04.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I know something you don't, Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.64,1:16:06.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Like what?!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.75,1:16:08.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.55,1:16:12.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. Just don't get in my way.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.82,1:16:17.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's hear the tape with the will for now. What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.86,1:16:19.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.00,1:16:26.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Detective?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.20,1:16:32.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or so I'd like to say, but the will can wait until after my explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.11,1:16:37.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After I've revealed who was responsible for the two incidents here.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.31,1:16:38.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.85,1:16:40.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start with the second incident,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.85,1:16:45.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with the hidden bow gun that was aimed at Mr. Yoshifusa.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.05,1:16:49.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now. Wasn't the guy with the sunglasses behind that?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.42,1:16:51.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.62,1:16:54.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Until I heard a certain someone say a certain something.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.96,1:16:56.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Certain something?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.53,1:17:00.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we give it a listen? We do have it...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.30,1:17:03.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,on Side B of the will tape.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.84,1:17:06.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Attorney. Please play it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.44,1:17:07.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.88,1:17:14.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Let's play it and see.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.05,1:17:15.78,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Duck!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.78,1:17:17.42,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Look out!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.42,1:17:18.69,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.69,1:17:22.36,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}T-The cabinet! An arrow came out of that cabinet!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.36,1:17:23.59,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.59,1:17:25.46,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A c-crossbow!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.46,1:17:27.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what about this?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.16,1:17:29.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it seem strange?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.46,1:17:35.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As you all know, the arrow fired from the cabinet
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.20,1:17:37.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,flew across the room in an instant,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.80,1:17:41.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,shot through the wall, and left our field of vision.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.81,1:17:46.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, a certain person accurately identified it as an arrow,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.71,1:17:51.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,before we even opened the cabinet and found a crossbow inside.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:51.55,1:17:53.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would that be?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.92,1:17:56.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Keiko! Don't tell me you...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.82,1:17:59.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The answer is simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.89,1:18:05.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was because {\i1}you{\i0} set up that crossbow, Keiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.90,1:18:07.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.50,1:18:11.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that's not enough to prove Keiko did it...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.64,1:18:17.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true! I set it up! The day Uncle Yoshifusa came back!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.44,1:18:19.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Keiko...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.78,1:18:23.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got us in debt. I kept it a secret from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.58,1:18:27.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a huge amount, with even bigger interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.15,1:18:30.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought if I could get my portion of the inheritance,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.02,1:18:34.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I could pay it all off without you ever knowing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:34.46,1:18:41.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, when I heard your uncle came back from Brazil, I just snapped.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.23,1:18:43.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't intend to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.54,1:18:47.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to scare him enough to return to Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.81,1:18:51.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I set it up so it'd miss him.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.14,1:18:55.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect it to fly so close to him!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.28,1:18:59.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter,\Nsince you killed Mother anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.69,1:19:00.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.82,1:19:03.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was your doing too, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.06,1:19:06.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! That wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.16,1:19:08.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.76,1:19:11.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth! Believe me!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.36,1:19:13.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.77,1:19:18.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who murdered Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand hid her in the well...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.17,1:19:19.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was someone else!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.74,1:19:22.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.14,1:19:23.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who?!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.06,1:19:25.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it?!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.08,1:19:28.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Okay! Solve this right, Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.82,1:19:31.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The person responsible...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.18,1:19:33.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We'll be watching!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.53,1:19:40.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.43,1:19:45.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who murdered Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand hid her body in the well...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.97,1:19:50.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Don't tell us it was\Nthe guy with the sunglasses!
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.44,1:19:54.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably our mom's brother, who blames us
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.38,1:20:00.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,for her death when she fell into the well 15 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.58,1:20:05.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He has a motive, but could you save this for until {\i1}after{\i0} he's caught?!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.65,1:20:08.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. He's likely a detective someone hired
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.49,1:20:13.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to determine if Mr. Yoshifusa really is who he claims to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.43,1:20:17.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hold on. If he's not the killer, then...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.33,1:20:19.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't mean...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.13,1:20:26.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s killer is in this very room!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.64,1:20:33.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now! You heard that she called from the hotel at 9:00 last night!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.61,1:20:38.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if she left right after calling,\Nshe'd arrive here after 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.65,1:20:42.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We were all in the same room then,\Nso we couldn't have done it!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.89,1:20:45.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Might {\i1}this{\i0} be possible?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.69,1:20:49.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just after 8:00, Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made her first call from the party,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.76,1:20:52.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then left the party immediately after.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.47,1:20:56.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just after 9:00, she parked the car in the woods
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.20,1:21:00.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and played back a tape recording of the party on the car stereo
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.78,1:21:02.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while making her second call.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.98,1:21:06.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To make it seem as if she was still at the party.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.81,1:21:12.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She was the one who was killed.\NWhy would she create an alibi?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.79,1:21:15.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because things wound up just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.92,1:21:16.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Opposite?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.92,1:21:19.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.66,1:21:26.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} planned to use that alibi trick and kill someone.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.47,1:21:30.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But she wound up being killed by that person instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.94,1:21:32.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.84,1:21:42.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ironically, her trick wound up helping the alibi of her killer instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.52,1:21:44.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The raincoat found in the well...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.95,1:21:51.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She put it on beforehand to keep her victim's blood off her clothes.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.93,1:21:54.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the camellia flower...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.30,1:21:59.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She had it in her pocket so she could drop it at the murder scene later
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.30,1:22:04.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it look connected to the incident 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.97,1:22:07.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As for the tape lying by the firewood,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.21,1:22:13.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she either dropped it on her way to her target who was in the bath,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.41,1:22:21.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,or it fell from her pocket while her body was being carried to the well.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.19,1:22:27.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In either case, she likely planned to burn the tape in the stove.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.66,1:22:32.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murder probably happened in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.93,1:22:38.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, if any blood went flying,\Nit could be cleaned away.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.44,1:22:43.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, who is this person who killed her first in the bathroom?!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.54,1:22:49.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s target was someone fond of taking a bath every day,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.35,1:22:53.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the only person here whose turn to use it was set in stone.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.29,1:22:57.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you, Yoshifusa Yabu'uchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.09,1:23:01.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Uncle?! That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.96,1:23:06.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, Brazilian jiu-jutsu has a certain technique...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.70,1:23:09.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in which you twist the arm of a knife-wielding attacker
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.50,1:23:12.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and cause the attacker to stab himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.54,1:23:18.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} attacked,\Nyou used that move without thinking!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.21,1:23:23.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Increasing her share of the inheritance was probably her motive.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.55,1:23:29.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that would be self-defense.\NWhy would he keep quiet about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.32,1:23:35.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he had been sent {\i1}two{\i0} threatening letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.63,1:23:40.07,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So, there's still another cretin out to take my life.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.07,1:23:44.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That clearly indicates someone had attacked him before.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.87,1:23:48.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, Machiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had also sent a threat letter.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.34,1:23:51.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Keiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had set up the arrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.81,1:23:55.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume he tied the body to the well rope and made it easy to spot
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.95,1:23:59.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to serve as an example to the other intimidator.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.39,1:24:05.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, it was self-defense, plain and simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.59,1:24:10.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you confess, Yoshifusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.10,1:24:12.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You still have room for improvement.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.94,1:24:17.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Who're you?!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.01,1:24:22.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The man with the sunglasses!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.58,1:24:23.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.98,1:24:29.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The tape with the will on it.\NOne listen will shed light on everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.18,1:24:30.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.45,1:24:32.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.45,1:24:38.69,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I divide my inheritance between the following six people:
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.69,1:24:43.73,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}my wife Machiko, my daughter Hiromi, her husband Hidekazu,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.73,1:24:47.00,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}my son Yoshiyuki, his wife Keiko,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.00,1:24:49.87,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and Carlos.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.87,1:24:55.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Carlos?! W-What is his name doing on here?!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.48,1:25:00.35,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I hereby divide my inheritance evenly among those six people.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.35,1:25:04.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange! Why isn't your name on the list, Uncle?!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.89,1:25:07.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.59,1:25:12.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, that old man is a bodyguard who came here from Brazil
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.96,1:25:15.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep Carlos safe!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.80,1:25:17.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.50,1:25:21.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, who is Carlos?!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.17,1:25:27.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The son born of the real Yoshifusa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and a Brazilian woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.04,1:25:29.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Son?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.04,1:25:32.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Detective! Where did you find that out?!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.65,1:25:35.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not a detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.38,1:25:40.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just a mere mystery writer.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.02,1:25:41.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.56,1:25:44.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yikes! D-Dad!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.39,1:25:46.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! What are {\i1}you{\i0} doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.93,1:25:50.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uhh, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.16,1:25:53.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But is he really not him?!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.77,1:25:56.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's left-handed, and his handwriting matched!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.77,1:26:00.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The world is full of left-handed people.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.47,1:26:02.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural the handwriting matches.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.48,1:26:08.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Mr. Yoshifusa had the old man write for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.02,1:26:14.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Yoshifusa and the old man owned a farm in Brazil together.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.12,1:26:18.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when a tornado hit 10 years ago,\Nthe old man hurt his right leg
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.79,1:26:22.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and Mr. Yoshifusa lost his left arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.46,1:26:29.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since, the old man wrote for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.24,1:26:31.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Carlos was given part of the inheritance
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.74,1:26:35.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because Mr. Yoshichika felt sorry for his brother who lost his farm
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.98,1:26:40.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and had died of illness half a year prior.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.65,1:26:43.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all written in here,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.85,1:26:48.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,in this pile of letters left in a hidden panel in the storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.66,1:26:51.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did you pretend to be our uncle?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.09,1:26:53.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it was to pilfer money!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.16,1:26:57.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that was his intent,\Nhe wouldn't have taken on the role
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.16,1:26:59.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,of someone whose life was threatened.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.67,1:27:02.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If people learned Carlos was Mr. Yoshifusa's son,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.40,1:27:05.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he would've been targeted by the intimidators.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.31,1:27:09.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the old man\Ntook on the role of Mr. Yoshifusa.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.74,1:27:14.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,To have the intimidators' attacks focused on him instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.11,1:27:17.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is evidenced by the fact that when the old man would bathe,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.25,1:27:19.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he would leave Carlos in the other room.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.85,1:27:22.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Because making it seem like he was keeping watch over everyone
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.96,1:27:25.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,would be the safest idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.13,1:27:28.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The old man planned to catch the intimidator,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.00,1:27:30.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but wound up killing her instead.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.53,1:27:32.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Although it was a case of self-defense,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.97,1:27:37.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he would've been taken away by the police for questioning.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.10,1:27:42.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he couldn't leave Carlos alone with one other intimidator around.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.24,1:27:46.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He made the body easy to find to see if the police detective who came
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.41,1:27:49.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was a sensible man or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.58,1:27:53.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what came was an unreliable rookie detective.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.85,1:27:54.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With no other choice,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.86,1:28:00.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the old man decided to remain silent until the will was read.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.13,1:28:02.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.80,1:28:04.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I get anything wrong,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.93,1:28:07.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hickson Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, 2nd-generation Japanese-Brazilian?!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.67,1:28:13.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're exactly right. You didn't get a single thing wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.61,1:28:15.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll present yourself to the police,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.28,1:28:19.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can introduce you to a great, hardhearted inspector I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.81,1:28:24.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that would be best. I think I can trust you!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.02,1:28:31.03,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Inspector Megure arrived two hours later,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.03,1:28:36.63,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} and Keiko{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}\Nwere taken to the Gunma Police Dept.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.63,1:28:42.64,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Carlos, who knew very little Japanese, watched sadly as the car left,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:42.64,1:28:47.11,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}but Dad told him in Portuguese that he would be back very soon,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.11,1:28:51.38,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}at which he showed child-like joy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.38,1:28:54.78,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Apparently, in order to keep Carlos safe,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.78,1:28:57.32,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Tanaka{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} hadn't told him about the inheritance
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.32,1:29:02.76,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}or that this was his father's family's home.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.76,1:29:06.06,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And then, the long night ended.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.86,1:29:11.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! You heard my voice?!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.43,1:29:14.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Dr. Agasa gave me a microphone
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.00,1:29:17.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that picks up sounds from your bowtie.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.34,1:29:20.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It helped with my deduction.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.67,1:29:23.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I would've known the old man wasn't the real deal
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.68,1:29:25.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,if I'd found those letters, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.85,1:29:31.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I knew he was a fake before reading the letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.12,1:29:32.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How?!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.22,1:29:34.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,His leg scar.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.29,1:29:37.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A left-handed first baseman\Nwould stretch out from the left leg.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.76,1:29:40.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that old man's scar was on his right leg.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.93,1:29:47.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seemed strange, so I scoured the storeroom and found the letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.57,1:29:51.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you still lack in the observation department, Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.84,1:29:53.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You think you're so great.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.71,1:29:57.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you trying to act cool,\Nafter chasing after me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.48,1:30:01.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm just a mere mystery writer."\NYou gotta be kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.42,1:30:04.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to be Kogoro Akechi or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.05,1:30:07.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about lame! I can't believe you!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.65,1:30:09.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yukiko.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.53,1:30:13.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.16,1:30:17.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. You don't care how others feel.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.66,1:30:20.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"We leave"? Don't insult me!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.74,1:30:27.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing, Shin'ichi? You'll get left behind!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.51,1:30:29.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.18,1:30:36.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In any event, these incidents\Nand this marital spat are over now.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.07,1:32:05.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.59,1:32:07.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Give Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} my regards!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.27,1:32:11.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes. I'd watch out for Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.88,1:32:16.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something bugs me about that last smile of hers...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.72,1:32:20.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Underestimate women and you'll be in a world of hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.62,1:32:22.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You {\i1}do{\i0} understand!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.89,1:32:25.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.93,1:32:29.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}She can't be serious... can she?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.56,1:32:33.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.37,1:32:35.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,home?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.04,1:32:38.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Dr. Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.57,1:32:40.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Heard what?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.17,1:32:46.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going on an overnight trip somewhere, at least tell us first!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.25,1:32:47.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.72,1:32:51.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried sick!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.45,1:32:54.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I kept calling Shin'ichi's house\Nbut no one was there!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.79,1:32:55.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, now!
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.88,1:32:58.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.93,1:33:02.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}D-Don't scare me like that...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.85,1:33:08.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A syringe! What is she planning to do?!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.21,1:33:13.41,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.41,1:33:14.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Chloroform...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.59,1:33:24.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It was probably poison she put in the wine!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.01,1:33:26.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}How does she plan to use it?!
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.10,1:33:33.99,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
